    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Achillea millefolium are its antioxidant effects, which are attributed to the presence of flavonoids and phenolic acids, helping to protect cells from oxidative damage. The plant's anti-inflammatory properties, mediated by sesquiterpene lactones and essential oils, contribute to its ability to reduce inflammation and alleviate associated symptoms. Additionally, Achillea millefolium exhibits antimicrobial activity, primarily due to its content of volatile oils and terpenes, which inhibit the growth of various microorganisms. Its antispasmodic effects, attributed to the presence of sesquiterpene lactones and flavonoids, help to relax muscles and alleviate spasms. Furthermore, the plant's analgesic properties, which are associated with the presence of sesquiterpene lactones and essential oils, contribute to its pain-relieving effects.",
