    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Achillea millefolium are luteolin, apigenin, rosmarinic acid, achillin, and quercetin, which contribute to its anti-inflammatory, antioxidant, and antimicrobial properties. Luteolin and apigenin, both flavonoids, have been shown to inhibit pro-inflammatory enzymes and cytokines, reducing inflammation and oxidative stress. Rosmarinic acid, a phenolic acid, has potent antioxidant and anti-inflammatory effects, scavenging free radicals and inhibiting the production of pro-inflammatory mediators. Achillin, a sesquiterpene lactone, has been found to have anti-inflammatory and antimicrobial activities, while quercetin, a flavonoid, has been shown to have antioxidant, anti-inflammatory, and immunomodulatory effects. The combination of these constituents in Achillea millefolium makes it a valuable herbal remedy for various health conditions, including wound healing, pain management, and gastrointestinal disorders.",
