    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Achillea millefolium are derived from its leaves and flowers, which are rich in bioactive compounds. Tea made from the dried flowers and leaves is traditionally used to aid digestion, reduce fever, and alleviate menstrual cramps, due to its anti-inflammatory and antispasmodic properties. A tincture of Achillea millefolium is used to treat anxiety, insomnia, and restlessness, as it contains flavonoids and sesquiterpenes with sedative and anxiolytic effects. A salve or topical cream prepared from the plant's essential oil and infused in a carrier oil is applied to the skin to treat wounds, burns, and bruises, thanks to its antimicrobial and anti-inflammatory properties. Infusions of Achillea millefolium flowers and leaves are also used to treat respiratory issues such as bronchitis and coughs, due to the presence of camphor and other volatile oils with expectorant and anti-inflammatory effects, while its essential oil is used in aromatherapy to promote relaxation and reduce stress.",
